This anelastic test case is based on the anelastic Jupiter model dynamo 
 Jones 2014, Icarus 241 p 148-159.
The equations are the same as used in the unified version, so no rescaling is required.
 Ra-unified = 1.1d07. Pr=0.1, Pm=3, E=2.5d-05 radius ratio =0.0963. The reference state is 
a Jupiter model given in French et al. 2012. The reference state model is in planet_model.txt.in,
generated by matlab script jupiter_model_finalsmooth2_paper.m.  
 
At i_N=128 i_L=128 and i_Mp=1, i_M=128  the solution is fully time-dependent, as described 
in the paper. The magnetic energy flucuates by a factor 2 with a mean around 3.1d06 and the KE
 fluctuates with a mean of around 1.5d06.

The run is in a similar parameter regime to those of published anelastic dynamo models, as so
the computational load is more typical of research production runs than the benchmarks.
   


